ways of deployment: 
1. via UI: add a yaml file straightaway
2. import from a Git repo
3. via CLI: 
    a. git clone to local machine
    b. get into the application folder
    c. oc apply -f ./file-name.yaml    //in Linux; .\ in windows



3 types of users:
regular users
system users: to interact with infrastructure, some are created by default
service accounts

OpenShift master includes a built-in OAuth server for authenticating and authorising users into clusters
for all-in-one mode of setup, the default of OAuth config value is AllowAllIdentityProvider in /etc/origin/master/master-config.yanl, it allows all users logging in without verifying passwords,
if a user doesnt exist, it auto-creates it. 
the value can be set to DenyAllIdentityProvider which would stop all users logging in, in this case, admin has to manually create and enable new users.

oc get users
there are default projects created, but system admin couldnt login UI, so a new clusteradmin user needs to be created and enabled 
by running oc admin policy add-cluster-role-to-user, then now built-in projects would be visible again.
